  "title": "Electrical/Electronic Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title:</strong> Electrical/Electronic Engineer</p>\n<p><strong>Location:</strong> Singapore</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>About Us:</strong> We are a leading AI and robotics company at the forefront of technological innovation, dedicated to creating cutting-edge solutions that revolutionize industries. As we continue to grow, we are seeking talented Electrical/Electronic Engineers to join our team.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description:</strong> dConstruct is looking for electrical/electronic engineers to join our vibrant and driven systems integration team working on solving challenging problems in robotics. As an electrical/electronic engineer at dConstruct, you will be designing, building and integrating robotic systems needed to solve complex real-world problems. You will be working with clients to understand their needs and, in turn, implement their requirements accordingly.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>1. Electrical and Electronic circuit design for robotics systems, actuators, sensors and systems integration.</p>\n<p>2. Create schematics and PCB layouts for power distribution modules, motor driver circuits, actuator control electronics, peripheral and sensor interfaces.</p>\n<p>3. Prototype and debug electrical and electronic circuits.</p>\n<p>4. Create specifications and design schemes.</p>\n<p>5. Select components and vendors.</p>\n<p>6. Work with internal/external partners to support manufacture of sub-systems.</p>\n<p>7. Work on cross functional systems design and test with mechanical, software, and robotics engineers.</p>\n<p>8. Diagnose and resolve technical issues.</p>\n<p>9. Define test plans and evaluate reliability.</p>\n<p>10. Testing, deployment and commissioning of systems.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements and Skills:</strong></p>\n<p>1. Bachelor's degree in electrical engineering, electronics engineering, or other related fields.</p>\n<p>2. 5+ years experience in electrical/electronic design engineering.</p>\n<p>3. Experience in power distribution modules, motor driver circuits, actuator control electronics, peripheral and sensor interfaces.</p>\n<p>4. Experience and knowledge in robotics fields is preferred.</p>\n<p>5. Experience with PCB design and PCB design software such as KiCAD or Altium</p>\n<p>6. Basic knowledge of C/C++.</p>\n<p>7. Familiarity with sensors, actuators and design constraints common to robotic systems</p>\n<p>8. Familiarity with industrial safety standards.</p>\n<p>9. Good technical communication skills</p>\n<p>10. Able to work independently with some guidance</p>",
